      <description>&lt;p&gt;Here&amp;rsquo;s an article in English explaining Zero-Knowledge Proofs:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;understanding-zero-knowledge-proofs&#34;&gt;Understanding Zero-Knowledge Proofs&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Zero-Knowledge Proof (ZKP) is a cryptographic method by which one party (the prover) can prove to another party (the verifier) that they know a value, fact, or piece of information without conveying any information apart from the fact that they possess that knowledge. Here are the key characteristics:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
